  "name": "SLE - ANA Antibody Titer Query (Positive)",
  "description": "Tests ability to find SLE patients via positive ANA (Antinuclear Antibody) titer. ANA is the primary screening lab for SLE \u2014 titers \u22651:160 (numerically encoded as 160 in our data) are clinically significant. Synthea generates ANA titers of 160-1280 for SLE patients (positive). The ANA test has high sensitivity (~95%) but lower specificity \u2014 many autoimmune conditions can produce positive ANA.",
  "prompt": "Find patients with positive antinuclear antibody (ANA) titer lab results at or above 160 \u2014 the clinical threshold for autoimmune disease workup.",
  "prompts": {
    "naive": "Find patients with positive ANA.",
    "broad": "Find patients with elevated antinuclear antibody (ANA) titer \u2014 values at or above 160 (1:160 dilution), the standard threshold for clinically significant ANA positivity.",
    "expert": "I need Observation resources with elevated ANA titer. Use LOINC code 5048-4 (Nuclear Ab [Titer] in Serum by Immunofluorescence). Filter by value-quantity at or above 160 (the standard 1:160 cutoff). Query: Observation?code=http://loinc.org|5048-4&value-quantity=ge160"
  },
